trans-unit.source: The :is() (formerly :matches(), formerly :any()) pseudo-class checks whether the element at its position in the outer selector matches any of the selectors in its selector list. It's useful syntactic sugar that allows you to avoid writing out all the combinations manually as separate selectors. The effect is similar to nesting in Sass and most other CSS preprocessors.

The :matches() (formerly :any()) pseudo-class checks whether the element at its position in the outer selector matches any of the selectors in its selector list. It's useful syntactic sugar that allows you to avoid writing out all the combinations manually as separate selectors. The effect is similar to nesting in Sass and most other CSS preprocessors.
trans-unit.target: La :matches() (antes :any() ) comprueba si el elemento en su posición en el selector externo coincide con alguno de los selectores en su lista de selectores. El efecto es similar al anidamiento en Sass y la mayoría de los demás preprocesadores CSS.

trans-unit.source: The input event is fired when the user changes the value of an <input> element, <select> element, or <textarea> element. By contrast, the "change" event usually only fires after the form control has lost focus.

trans-unit.target: El atributo inputmode especifica qué tipo de mecanismo de entrada sería más útil para los usuarios que ingresan contenido en el control de formulario.

trans-unit.source: The loading attributing on images & iframes gives authors control over when the browser should start loading the resource.

trans-unit.target: El método localeCompare() devuelve un número que indica si una cadena de referencia viene antes o después o es la misma que la cadena dada en el orden de clasificación.

trans-unit.source: The padStart() and padEnd() methods pad the current string with a given string (eventually repeated) so that the resulting string reaches a given length. trans-unit.target: Los padStart() y padEnd() la cadena actual con una cadena dada (eventualmente repetida) para que la cadena resultante alcance una longitud determinada.
